column12: It's very friendly and helpful. It is a good introduction to the shell.
column13: Although, new users might appreciate pointers on where to go to learn more after this short introduction. Also, maybe have arrows to skip commands or man pages for the curious readers.

column12: The ability to easily create automated tasks
column13: The presentation of the options could use more work. At the moment it looks like it presents as if it were any other shell in the sense that it just lists the files. It would be easier if there were some categorization , especially considering commands that have an extremely long list of options or subcommands. This is probably pedantic, but it also wasn't clear that there was a git repository when removing index.
